<br>
It should be a fairly quiet board, but at the same time it should be able to be used as a reference for most players.  Using the General section is difficult for that, because threads drop into obscurity so fast they often do not recieve a decent answer.<br>
<br>
I would say to combine the Sorcerer's Tower with with Apprentices' Hall, except that then you will get a lot of people bashing others.  It will always happen, I've been around the internet for a long time, and you always have bitter Dino's bashing newbies for asking a question for the billionth time.  How many times has someone asked what the Flowing Thought cap is and gotten bashed for it on the general section?<br>
<br>
I also think that the Sorcerer's section would be a good place to work on FAQ's for wizards of differing levels (which could then be made into a guide) Such as the Cradle to Grave threads. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lunaltoadsnatcher>Lunal Toadsnatcher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1358<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/7/03 8:41:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26402.topic&index=52>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What can we do to improve the message boards?</span><hr size=1> Ya know if he new board started off with a pay section and a free section the pay section is guaranteed to ward off a high percentage of the griefing types, esp. the jihaders.  Most of the true contributors would pay, based on their ezboard track record. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=myztic>MyztiC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Born-Again Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 929<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/7/03 9:14:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26402.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What can we do to improve the message boards?</span><hr size=1> There is good faq stuff in library at the moment about FT caps and all kinds of stuff like that, but it is still sorta pointless when newbies don't bother to search / look for answers, they want to be catered to.<br>
<br>
Instead of having merged highlevel / newbie question board, mods pointing people to FAQ section / guides and locking threads with comment about those, I'd say pretty soon people would start to make use of those. There are other boards where such behavior (search before posting) is strictly enforced by mods and those boards don't seem to suffer from it at all. Quite contrary, they seem to be less cluttered with same questions on pages 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, etc.<br>
<br>
Such moderation might make it actually feasible to ditch those two forums and then keep the questions / discussions in General board. But are wizards ready for such change? <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#ffffff>- </font><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation>Graffë's Wizard Discussion</a><font color=#ffffff> - </font><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1>General EQ Discussion</a> <font color=#ffffff> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.240<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

